    "summary": "Lindenbergh Investments is led by Mrs. Esther Boers-de Vries who was educated in The Netherlands as an international tax lawyer (LL.M., University of Leiden, The Netherlands, graduated in 1997). She worked for the well-known international law office Loyens & Loeff in Europe (The Netherlands and Luxembourg office) focusing on integrated worldwide corporate law and tax practices till 2005.\n\nDuring 2005 she moved to the Middle East (Kingdom of Saudi Arabia and the United Arab Emirates) where she worked as an international tax and corporate lawyer for KMPG where she gained substantial experience in setting up worldwide tax-efficient corporate and fund structures. \n\nIn 2010 she founded the first office in the Middle East for the Vistra Group in the Dubai International Financial Centre (United Arab Emirates) where she became a Board Member of Vistra's Management Board and Partner of the Vistra Group. Since then she has been growing and managing the Vistra Group's presence in the Middle East and wider region. During the summer of 2016 she launched the Middle East Desk for Vistra in Amsterdam (The Netherlands).\n\nIn 2017 she left the Vistra Group to focus on private financial family affaires in Europe. Lindenbergh Investments was created.",
